**Fortune 2024: Fidelity National Information Services Overview**

Fidelity National Information Services (FIS), a leading provider of financial data services, ranks 288th on the prestigious Fortune 2024 list, marking a decline of 5 positions from its previous ranking. The company, listed on the stock exchange under the ticker symbol FIS, operates within the Business Services sector, specifically in the Financial Data Services industry.

Headquartered in Jacksonville, Florida, FIS has a significant presence with approximately 60,000 employees worldwide. The company's website can be found at https://www.fisglobal.com. As a publicly traded entity, FIS is subject to the scrutiny and expectations of the financial community.

Under the leadership of CEO Stephanie L. Ferris, who is notably one of the few female CEOs in the industry, FIS has navigated the complexities of the financial services landscape. Although Ferris is not the founder of the company, she has been instrumental in shaping its strategic direction.

Despite its scale, FIS has experienced a decline in its ranking, indicating a challenging period for the organization. The company's revenue growth has been modest, with a 1% increase in revenues, amounting to $14,680 million. However, this growth has not translated to profitability, as FIS reported a loss of $6,654 million. This decline in profitability is a concern, and the company will need to re-evaluate its strategies to regain profitability.

In terms of assets, FIS boasts a substantial portfolio valued at $55,105 million. Its market capitalization, as of March 28, 2024, stands at $42,762.2 million. While the company is not a newcomer to the Fortune 500 list, it has not been recognized as one of the World's Most Admired Companies or one of the Best Companies to Work For.

FIS's performance highlights the challenges facing companies in the financial data services industry. As the company continues to navigate this complex landscape, it will be crucial to adapt and innovate to remain competitive. With its significant resources and employee base, FIS is well-positioned to address these challenges and regain its footing in the market.